OL,6,F"This is an extremely sad case in
OL,7,Fwhich the driving decisions made by
OL,8,FGriffiths that day have led to
OL,9,Fdevastating consequences. Not just for
OL,10,FHarry's family and friends, but indeed
OL,11,Ffor his own.
OL,13,F"I would like to praise the actions of
OL,14,Fmembers of the public who stopped to
OL,15,Fhelp, administer first aid and provide
OL,16,Fcare which enabled Harry to survive in
OL,17,Fhospital for a further two days. This
OL,18,Fprovided his loved ones with the
OL,19,Fability to spend some precious final
OL,20,Fmoments with him.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/6
